A community in Tshwane battles to celebrate Diwali without water. PRETORIA - While Diwali lamps are lighting up their homes, their taps are running dry. For Laudium residents, the shortage of water has dampened the festival of lights. They say the shortages always happen around this time of year. During this religious period, families give back to communities. READ: Tshwane residents urged to save water But the water situation brought many hiccups. "We had to ask people who had saved water to come and come give us water to assist us," said Reggie Naidoo, a priest in the community. "It has been a mission, but everybody came to the table with whatever water they had at home." This community has one wish for Diwali and that's to have the water flowing again.